  "history": {
    "en": "Developed in the Austrian Alps during the mid-19th century as a durable scent hound for tracking wounded deer, boar, and hare over rugged terrain. Descended from larger Austrian hounds crossed with Dachshunds, it was a favorite of Crown Prince Rudolf of Habsburg and is officially recognized by the FCI.",
    "zh": "19世纪中期在奥地利阿尔卑斯地区培育而成，是一种耐用的嗅觉猎犬，用于在崎岖地形追踪受伤的鹿、野猪和野兔。由大型奥地利猎犬与腊肠犬杂交而来，曾是哈布斯堡王朝鲁道夫王储的最爱，并获FCI正式认可。"
